    "body": "> I was thinking of that, but didn't want to bloat the PR. Number should indeed be allowed too, even though it gets coerced to a string. Today it already works as `animal.cats.1.name`, but that's not very discoverable.\r\n\r\nAh right. My bad. Not `animal.cats[1].name` but `animal.cats.1.name`.\r\n\r\nWhat I wanted to ask you was,\r\n\r\n```\r\nfunction getPropertyByPath(\r\n  const parts = path.split('.');\r\n  object: object | undefined,\r\n  path: string | string[]\r\n)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat if the type of `path` is `string | Array<string | number>`. Does it make sense?",
